# Active Subagent Count Logging

When spawning and completing subagents, always emit a plain-text log line in your response at each lifecycle event.

- On subagent start: output a line like `[agent:start] <description> (active: N)`
- On subagent completion: output a line like `[agent:done] <description> (active: N)`

Where N is the running count of currently active (not yet completed) subagents. Track this count yourself across the response.
